Natural Eye Look Tutorial 1. Pick an eyeshadow shade that is close to your own skin color. 2. Apply the base. Moisturize if start with a clean surface. Cover your eyelids with eyeshadow primer, concealer. 3. Apply the lightest shade onto your inner eye to blend the edge until you cannot tell where the transition is. Repeat with a slightly darker shade and blending at the edge. 4. For a more defined style, pick a single shade. Blend it thoroughly over the crease, plus a small amount in your upper V. Use a thick brush in a rounded motion. This should leave you with a visible circle of eyeshadow, but in a subtle shade. 5. Draw eyeshadow slightly darker than your skin tone along your crease. Using a thick brush upward almost to your brow bone, thinning it into a smoky effect. 6. Brighten your eyes with a small addition. Dab a small dot of white or light tan eyeshadow on the corner of your eye, near your tear ducts.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My Natural Eye Shadows
reviews.reviewText: This is the best collection of eye shadows I've ever purchased in my life. The colors are natural and goes with everything I wear. Brings out the natural beauty in your eyes. Ill.purchase it again when I run out. It's worth buying ladies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dupe for FIVE Urban Decay NAKED palettes!
reviews.reviewText: This palette is less than $20 and is a dupe for FIVE Urban Decay NAKED palettes 😱Dupes of palettes are- NAKED 1, 2, 3, Cherry, and Honey. Each NAKED palette is around $60. 60×5 = $300! That’s a savings of over $280 🤯The quality is mind-blowing for the price. These shimmers are stunning. I own a couple of NAKED palettes and these are extremely similar in both color story and quality.I’m shook.Do not sleep on this palette!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I was completely shocked at the quality of this palette compared to the price. Usually when you get a lot of colors for a small price you get poor quality but that is not the case here. These shadows are very pigmented! They also blend very nicely. They have very good staying power as well. The brushes aren’t bad either, very soft and pick up product well.The first two pictures are the color swatched over concealer, the third is some swatches over a black primer, the third is and example of how well they blend (I’m not great at make up but you get the idea!), fourth is of a quick look I did and the fifth is the palette in regular house lighting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2021
reviews.reviewText: The makeup colors are great and cover well. The brushes are poorly made but I just saw them as an extra for the price being so fair.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly as described

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Impressive presentation, just doesn't quite hit the mark
reviews.reviewText: This palette seems to be one that will give Urban Decay or Morphe a run for their money. The shadows feel very soft, and I’m looking forward to trying them later for date night. It comes with this set of brushes, which is a nice touch, tho they’ll be my travel brushes. I took the pic with an ink pen across just to give an idea of the size of the shadow pots. They’re not big, and I feel like I’ll probably run out of the favorite ones quickly.I’ll amend my review after I give it a try!UPDATE: Okay- So I've used it a lot since my initial review. As far as staying power, I'd probably only give it 2 stars. Even with primer my shadow was near non-existent after about 5 hours of wear. Pigmentation- 2 stars. The colors I thought would be dramatic really weren't, and I felt like I had to really build it up. Those colors I did use were very blendable, however. Over all, it's an okay interim palette until I have time and money to get the better brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice Quality & Soft Colors
reviews.reviewText: Great variety of soft colors. Very nice quality. Long-lasting wearability. Offer so many color choices that would allow you to be able to mix colors to create additional colors. The brushes that comes with the eyeshadows palette are of very good quality. No worries about brittle falling out. Would purchase again but going for another color scheme. High recommend. 👏😊
